## CPPC Informer access

The CPPC informer is already guarded by `enableCPPCInformer` (a separate, independent flag — not subject to mutual exclusion). When running `--enable-metrics-aggregator`, you pass `--enable-cppc-informer` alongside it, and the `MetricsAggregatorReconciler` accesses the cached config via `clusterpodplacementconfig.GetClusterPodPlacementConfig()` — exactly the same pattern used by other modes. No additional wiring is needed; the informer is added as a runnable to the manager before any mode-specific controllers start.

